  faqs={[
    { question: "Can it ingest storm-map / weather lead vendors?", answer: "Yes. We integrate with HailTrace, Weather Decision Technologies, CompanyCam, Hover and most storm-lead vendors via API or webhook. Leads land in your pipeline with the storm event already tagged." },
    { question: "Do you replace AccuLynx or JobNimbus?", answer: "We can either replace them with a custom build or integrate on top — depends on what your team uses. Custom usually wins when your sales motion is unique or your claim workflow is complex." },
    { question: "Will my crews actually use it?", answer: "We design the field app to be 3 taps from photo to job. If a crew lead can text a customer, they can use it. We also onboard crews in-person or over video to make sure adoption sticks." },
    { question: "Can we keep using QuickBooks for accounting?", answer: "Yes. We sync deposits, invoices, supplier bills and job cost back to QuickBooks (Online or Desktop) so your bookkeeper keeps the same workflow." },
    { question: "How long until we go live?", answer: "Most roofing rollouts are live in 4–8 weeks: 2 weeks discovery + design, 3–4 weeks build, 1–2 weeks pilot and training. Insurance-heavy operations skew toward the longer end." },
    { question: "What does it cost?", answer: "Custom roofing systems typically start around $8K–$25K for the build, plus a small monthly for hosting + support. We scope after the operational assessment so you know exactly what you're getting before committing." },
